 Police Spokesperson Colonel Mtsholi Bhembe, said that an unknown man entered the church while Pastor Christopher Mokwena was conducting a service. The man forced the pastor out of the church at gunpoint. Also read: Three killed in shootout with Police The suspect told the congregants to continue with the service as he had some business to take care of with their pastor. Members of the church contacted the police. When the SAPS arrived on the scene they found Pastor Mokwena lying in a pool of blood, about 200 matres away from the church.
The deceased sustained bullet wounds on his upper body and was declared dead at the scene. Also read: Nigerian assassinated in front of house Police have opened a murder case. Anyone with information that could assist police is urged to contact Detective Constable Lazarus Mtshweni at 072 947 3661.  Suspects might be linked to seven other robberies • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za